Exposure Instability Analysis of Signature Exposures with Bootstrap

Source: R/sig_fit_bootstrap_batch.R
sig_fit_bootstrap_batch.Rd

Exposure Instability Analysis of Signature Exposures with Bootstrap

sig_fit_bootstrap_batch(
  catalogue_matrix,
  methods = c("LS", "QP"),
  n = 100L,
  p_val_thresholds = c(0.05),
  use_parallel = FALSE,
  seed = 123456L,
  ...
)

Arguments

catalogue_matrix

a numeric matrix V with row representing components and columns representing samples, typically you can get nmf_matrix from sig_tally() and transpose it by t().
methods

a subset of c("LS", "QP", "SA").
n

the number of bootstrap replicates.
p_val_thresholds

a vector of relative exposure threshold for calculating p values.
use_parallel

if TRUE, use parallel computation based on furrr package, not implemented yet.
seed

random seed to reproduce the result.
...

other common parameters passing to sig_fit_bootstrap, including sig, sig_index, sig_db, db_type, mode, etc.

Value

a list of data.table.

See also

sig_fit, [sig_fit_bootstrap

Examples

W <- matrix(c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6), ncol = 2)
colnames(W) <- c("sig1", "sig2")
W <- apply(W, 2, function(x) x / sum(x))

H <- matrix(c(2, 5, 3, 6, 1, 9, 1, 2), ncol = 4)
colnames(H) <- paste0("samp", 1:4)

V <- W %*% H
V
#>         samp1 samp2    samp3 samp4
#> [1,] 1.666667   2.1 2.566667   0.7
#> [2,] 2.333333   3.0 3.333333   1.0
#> [3,] 3.000000   3.9 4.100000   1.3

if (requireNamespace("lsei") & requireNamespace("quadprog")) {
  z <- sig_fit_bootstrap_batch(V, sig = W, n = 10)
  z
}
